post_text: Since 2002, Rhinebeck schools have been observing a morning moment of silence on 9/11 for those individuals killed in the 9/11/01 terrorist attacks. New York State has now designated 9/11 as Remembrance Day and made it a requirement for schools to observe this moment of silence.

post_text: Many students walk and/or ride bicycles to/from school. For student safety, motorists must come to a complete stop at Stop signs, heed yellow student pedestrian signs, and yield to walkers crossing the street, in marked crosswalks, at corners, and in the middle of streets.

post_text: NY schools are back in session, starting today, Wed, Sept 4. Passing a school bus with its lights on, stopped OR in the process of stopping, is extremely dangerous for students boarding or exiting the bus, AND is a violation of NYS Motor Vehicle law. Keep our children safe!

post_text: As many already know, the RCSD website has been up and down sporadically over the past several days. Since we have no degree of confidence right now about when it will be up consistently, we're not going to announce that it IS back up until we know that for sure.

post_text: Due to technical difficulties beyond our control, our website and also our VOIP phone system are both down today. We believe that one or both issues may be related to the weekend storm. We're working on getting both systems back soon. Thank you again for your patience.
